text: Muhammad Ali Taher Parasong (9 February 1961 â€“ 3 January 2021) was an Indonesian politician. He was a member of the National Mandate Party. Taher was born in Lamakera, Indonesia. He was a member of the People's Representative Council from 1997 to 1999 and again from 2014 until his death. Taher died on 3 January 2021 in Jakarta from COVID-19 at the age of 59. ==References== Category:1961 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in Jakarta Category:Indonesian politicians
